CLOSEThe Navajo Police Department confirmed that nine employees have tested positive for COVID-19 as of Wednesday.
The department is seeking the assistance of laboratories to test employees, especially as the department has a shortage of personal protective equipment.
The Navajo Nation includes parts of Arizona, New Mexico and Utah.
Navajo Nation Police Department sets up road blocks on the Navajo Nation to inform the public about the curfew from 8 p.m. to 5 a.m. as well as hand out pamphlets about COVID-19.
"As the numbers of positive cases increase across the Navajo Nation, so does our risk of being exposed," he continued.